prompt:
Fix a security gap on classic-laddie: auto-login is enabled (services.displayManager.autoLogin) but the screen is NOT locked immediately after login, leaving a 5-minute window where anyone at the keyboard has full access before hypridle locks the session.

The fix: add exec-once = [ "hyprlock" ] to the hyprland settings for classic-laddie, so the screen locks immediately after auto-login. This is already done in home/remoting.nix for johnny-walker (line 32).

The best place to add this is in flake.nix inside classic-laddie's home-manager config block (around line 121-128). Add an inline hyprland setting:

```nix
home-manager.users.${config.cosmo.user.default} = {
  imports = [
    ./home/server.nix
    ./home/dev.nix
    ./home/workstation.nix
    ./home/identities/personal.nix
  ];
  # Lock screen immediately on session start (auto-login is enabled)
  wayland.windowManager.hyprland.settings.exec-once = [ "hyprlock" ];
};
```

This ensures that even though SDDM auto-logs in, hyprlock immediately presents a password prompt, so physical access requires authentication.

Run nix flake check to validate the config before creating the PR. If that doesn't work, at minimum run: nix eval .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel --no-build 2>&1 | head -5 to check for eval errors.
